summary: It’s not queer baiting if the subtext is there in the original work and we’ve been told the possibility of an explicit on screen...
body:
It’s not queer baiting if the subtext is there in the original work and we’ve been told the possibility of an explicit on screen gay relationship doesn’t exist, and it would not be true to the canon if there was one. Please stop clogging my happy place with your complaints.

That said: in my opinion the story is not about the boys falling in love anyway, that is a realization that happens post the events of book with the development and acknowledgement of buried feelings and both David and Michael get that and so far seem to pull it off perfectly.

Also, also, I’m well aware some of you are using queer baiting in a light hearted and sarcastic type of manner but I see many people who def. don’t mean it that way.

summary: Okay so I’m still freaking out about the trailer but a question that finally hit me was, where do these scene happen? Like the...
body: Okay so I’m still freaking out about the trailer but a question that finally hit me was, where do these scene happen? Like the wall scene doesn’t happen in the book so we don’t know where it’s from. Like where could it take place? An area in a church? The bookshop? Or maybe some where we haven’t been introduced to yet? And the scene with Adam looks like there is sand. Like is that Eden? I wonder where this ineffable duo will be going.

summary: Okay but the thing about “to the world,” the thing about that is!!!! Sheen said his goal as Aziraphale is to stare longingly at...
body: Okay but the thing about “to the world,” the thing about that is!!!! Sheen said his goal as Aziraphale is to stare longingly at Crowley without ever being caught at it and we’ve seen that all throughout the trailers, all that endless affection pinched back and restrained. This is a being whose spent 6000 years hiding his love from the world and himself going I don’t WANT to hide it anymore! And he lets it all go and and allows it to bloom on his face and in his voice as he looks Crowley in the eye and finally lets him see, ‘demon I have loved you for millennium and in this moment I want you to know it, all of it, no more shame and no more fear.’
